Program: Discovery
Title: The laser scanning opthalmoscope
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwg0
Last Broadcast Date: 15 May 1995
Scientists unveil retina laser scanning opthalmoscope. The scanner could help doctors understand how eyes, and eyesight, is affected as we age. Also, the Einstein-Podolsky-Rosen paradox in quantum theory - particles that communicate with each other faster than the speed of light and a new approach to treatment of Alzheimer's. Show less